VSYED MUTHAHAR SAQAFBombay Lakshmi Rajagopalan, an accomplished and talented Carnatic vocalist, recently gave a splendid concert at Rasika Ranjana Sabha, Tiruchi. With a crystal clear diction and amazing fluency, she wove a magic spell around the rasikas and transported them to a different world. Her selection of compositions for the programme was excellent.She has won many awards, honours and admirers and  Lakshmi has been recently made the Asthana Vidushi of Sakatapuram Sri Vidya Peetam which has conferred the title,  `Sangeeta Visharadha,' on her.Lakshmi began  the concert with a brisk varnam in Nattakurinji followed by `Mahaganapathim' in Naattai.The raga alapana of Harikhambodi followed by the famous kriti, `Rama Nannu Brovara' was  dealt with very well.Full of devotionThe viruttam in Hindolam, in praise of Paramacharya was full of devotion and bhakti. The main kriti, `Nidichala Sukhama,' of Tyagaraja  was  sung elaborately, followed by a thani avartanam. The latter half of the concert also was  captivating, with pieces including `Enna Thavam' in Kapi and `Appane Ayyappane' in Nadanamakriya.  Lakshmi concluded the concert with a tillana.Bottom Template Starts
